column2: Overcast and there has been intermittent rain for the last 2 days.
Sky hazy- partly sunny- rain forecast
Slight breeze- ripples on the water- and sunny.
Windy and rainy all week.  Cloudy and very hazy.
Clear- slight ripple on water- and lake level by bench marker is 2.05.
Sunshine- algae blooms- some weed cutting being done- water lilies in blossom- and the lake level at bench mark is 2 feet.
Clear weather- algae blooms- and lake level at bench mark is 1.97.
Weather clear- slight waves- larger boats running- algae blooms- and lake level at bench marker 1.86.
Partly cloudy- slight ripple- algae blooms- and lake level 1.8 by bench marker.
Sunny- rained earlier- water calm- and lake level at bench marker 2.27.
Sunny- slight ripple- algae blooms- lake level at bench marker 1.95.
Sunny- slight ripple on water- bench marker is at 1.8
Cloudy- slight waves- algae floating- bench mark level at 1.48.
Partly cloudy- raining off and on- algae floating as well as rising from the bottom- bench mark level at 1.68.
Sunny- few clouds- bench mark level at 1.45- last reading of the year.
Brown scum on shores out to 8 ft in water- cloudy- outer gauge used
Brown scum on shores 4-8 ft. out- cloudy- ripples
Algae blooms- brown scum 4-5 ft out- sunny- slight. ripple- 0.6" rain 8/9- .3" rain 8/13.  The rain gauge reading on 8/5 was 1.52 and on 8/8 the reading was 1.48.
1.1" rain 8/22.  The rain gauge reading on 8/18 was 1.42 inches.
1.36" rain.  The rain gauge reading on 8/25 was 1.36 inches.
Brown scum on shores- clear skies- small ripples on water
Brown scum on shores- cloudy skies- small ripples on water
4.6" rain in September- sunny- brown scum on shore- light ripple.  The rain gauge readings on 9/18 was 1.1- on 9/19 was 1.12- and on 9/23 was 1.36 inches.
Sunny- brown scum on shores settling- slight ripples on water- SW breeze- v. little boat activity
1.6" rain between 10/17 and 10/23- lake gauge out.  The rain gauge reading on 10/18 was 1.08 and on 10/25 the reading was also 1.08 inches.
Scum on shores- green silt on bottom- slightly cloudy- water calm
Clear- windy- waves 2-3 in.- lots of boats- still scum and green silt probs.
Partly cloudy- small waves- algae bloom
Clear sky- slight waves- floating scum- algae blooms
Heavy weed cover- bottom mucky- staff in but not checked
I have been on this lake 12 years and it is down considerably from the average.  Water level: up 3/4 inch from June 2
Water is bluish green.  Weed growth minimal because of use of aerators (2).
with Martin Billings--sample taken through hole in ice-covered lake
sunny- breezy- beautiful--no other people or boats seen
sunny- some wind- beatiful--water looks very clear

very windy- too windy to get any kind of accurate Secchi reading--no boats out- but three people were shore fishing--air temp 48.5 F very- very windy- too windy to take Secchi reading--sunny--air temp 48.5 F--no boats out- but three people shore fishing (no results)
cold and overcast--significant plant growth noted under the water- but only Brasenia on the surface
